Very pleased with Claw Daddy's Brooklyn. Great service by all staff members for the past 2 visits by us so far (both visits on a Friday afternoon 4:00-6:00PM). We always make sure to make a reservation prior. We truly enjoy the grilled oysters during happy hour ($1.50 every day until 5:00PM), also delicious to eat with their garlic bread. We also enjoy the adult caprisuns ($9 during happy hour). The king crab legs (1pound $44) are amazing! I was pleasantly surprised by the thickness of the crabmeat. We had our bag with the Claw Daddy's Special sauce and Medium spice level (potatoes and corn are included with the bag). We had one pound bag each and it was perfect! Last visit we also tried the Spicy Southern Deviled Eggs (4 halves for $6) and the Crab Cake Fritters (10 small sized balls for $11). We enjoyed the delived eggs, but were not impressed by the crab cake fritters.

My cousin wanted to come here to Claw Daddy's after an event to eat.  So I looked on line and read the reviews.  I quickly learned the best thing to do is make reservations.  The reviews of others overall to me was not bad and very helpful. Some like the adult Sun Capri drinks while one review stuck out to me. She said it was nasty another said couldn't really taste the pina colada taste. Well there we order them. I can say they are not cheap or stingy on the alcohol.  A little to strong for my liking. I had some called a little dream.  My cousin didn't like hers at all sent it back they took it off the bill😃 The bar had closed.  With mine they added more mixer and it tasted so much better!  They were so nice about it. My other cousin drink was bitter cause of the grapefruit skin still on.  Enough about the drinks.  The food for all 3 of us was on point!  We all enjoyed our food. We got the ball with shrimp, king crab legs. I order the saugauge,potatoes and corn. I shared my ssaugages so they could see how tasty they were.  They agreed. I'm the only one who got the Claw Daddy Sauce and my left overs at home I could lick my fingers. So good. I choice mild. One got the cheese and garlic and the other garlic butter. We all left happy campers. So I would say the drinks is where people have to know what they like. If want more flavor than over powering alcohol ask for less alcohol or more mixer.  They get two 👍 Up. We went to the one in Brooklyn 3rd avenue

Chose this place to surprise my friends with the wonderful news that I'm expecting. We had no reservations but we were seated immediately. I was really excited to try everything but our table was so small. We had to order little by little. The jambalaya was so good, and so was the mac and cheese.  The oysters were better than I expected they were juicy and had a hint of garlic and herbs which made them delicious. We had the King crab legs in medium spicy garlic butter and the spicy garlic butter.  The sauce was definitely not as spicy as they made it seem. To me the sauce was very bland it lacked so much flavor. I was disappointed because the sauce looked like it had so much flavor but It didnt. Had to fix it with more salt, extra hot sauce, and lemon. The king crab legs are pretty big and it came with corn and potatoes.  We ordered a lot of food but because it was so busy and packed I suppose our waiter forgot a lot of our food. He was trying his best. I would definitely go back to try more food off the menu and I would recommend bringing your favorite hot sauce, especially if you like really spicy food like me.  Honestly I ate a whole pound of seafood so if you love seafood this is the place for you and you dont need anyone to help you. I would have definitely ate more but our waiter forgot most of our order. I ate 30 oysters alone because of how good they were and they were $1.50 great price if you ask me.  My friends had drinks and they said they were pretty strong they come in these capri sun looking bags. So cute I guess it's a restaurant signature for their drinks. They even gave me soda in the bag. Overall it was a good experience. I'll definitely try it again on a less busy day. And I'll definitely bring my own sauce.

I went Claw Daddy's yesterday evening 8/3, and without a reservation we got seated right away, which was great, in the yard, which was fine for us. I think they can put some more lighting in the yard, so I wouldn't have to use my phone light to read the menu as well as to see the food I'm eating. I ordered the Crab Cake Fritters...nothing to write home about. I ordered the bag with shrimp, & opted for corn & potatoes as well. I hated the fact that I had no choice with the shrimp. It was "head on" only, and I really wanted shrimp, so I used the scissors provided to cut the heads off. I just didn't like that experience at all. I ordered the "Claw Daddy's Special" sauce which is supposed to be a combination of the other sauces with the  spicy" option, and it was all mehhh.  I have to say it was not my favorite at all. I did not enjoy it like I should have, and that could very well be because last week Friday  night, I ate at Cap't Loui aka Loui Loui uptown (on Broadway), and OM freaking G. Their shrimp bag with corn and potatoes was unbelievably delicious!!!! Sorry Claw Daddy's. What I really enjoyed  at Claw Daddy's was a drink...called "The French Quarter". That was good. I will return to Claw Daddy's to try the crab legs and have the same drink or maybe another. I have to stress, the employees were friendly and professional.
